article.headline: Stony Brook 77, Columbia 73
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Mitchell Beauford scored 27 points and Stony Brook came back from a 12-point deficit to beat Columbia 77-73 Saturday, spoiling the Lions' bid to begin a season 4-0 for the first time in 35 years. The Seawolves (2-1) trailed 60-50 with 9:40 left before going on a 17-7 run over the next six minutes. Beauford scored 10 points during the spurt. Columbia (3-1) pulled back in front, 71-69, on Matt Preston's layup with 2:43 to play but Bobby Santiago then banked in a 3-point shot with 2:09 left to put the Seawolves ahead for good. Stony Brook sealed the win with three free throws by Antwan Hardy in the final 14 seconds. Hardy finished with 17 points, Cori Spencer added 11 and Santiago had 10 for the Seawolves. Dragutin Kravic had 16 points, Preston had 15 and Mack Montgomery 13 for the Lions. Stony Brook was 25-for-31 from the foul line while the Lions were only 11 of 17.
